## 🔄 Iteration Strategy

### Week 1-2: Foundation
- Focus on Environment Validation + Rate Limiting
- Start Error Handling in parallel
- Establish monitoring baseline

### Week 3-4: Core Architecture  
- Complete Error Handling + Sidebar Refactor
- Begin Component Testing infrastructure
- Start Security implementations

### Week 5-6: Testing Foundation
- Complete Jest Setup + Component Tests
- Begin Storybook + Performance Testing
- Start E2E Enhancement

### Week 7-8: Quality & Monitoring
- Complete Performance Tests + Code Quality
- Finish Legacy Refactoring + Monitoring
- Final integration testing

---

## 🎯 Success Criteria by Phase

### Phase 1 Success (Weeks 1-4):
- [ ] Environment validation working
- [ ] Rate limiting prevents abuse
- [ ] Error boundaries catch all React errors
- [ ] Sentry tracking all exceptions
- [ ] Queries optimized with pagination
- [ ] Sidebar component < 200 lines
- [ ] Atomic components extracted
- [ ] Jest infrastructure operational
- [ ] Component tests > 80% coverage

### Phase 2 Success (Weeks 5-8):
- [ ] Storybook documenting all components
- [ ] Design system guidelines established
- [ ] Performance budgets enforced
- [ ] E2E tests cover critical user flows
- [ ] Code quality gates in CI/CD
- [ ] Legacy components refactored
- [ ] Monitoring dashboard operational
- [ ] Log management centralized

